-----------------------------------------------------------------
Static Socket Forwarding


ssh -N -L 0.0.0.0:<LISTENINGPORT>:<FORWARDEDIP>:<FORWARDEDPORT> <INTERMEDIARYSSHUSER>@<INTERMEDIARYIP> 

#This command uses the SSH utility with the -N flag to not display a shell and the -L flag to setup a local port forwarding, a port forwarding along a local network.
#The command accept as paramets the <LISTENINGPORT> of the first pawned machine, the <FORWARDEDIP> and <FORWARDEDPORT> of the target machine and ssh credentials of a 2ยบ pawned machine.

#Example; ssh -N -L 0.0.0.0:4455:172.16.50.217:445 database_admin@10.4.50.215

------------------------------------------------------------------
Dynamic Socket Forwarding


ssh -N -D 0.0.0.0:<LISTENINGPORT> <INTERMEDIARYSSHUSER>@<INTERMEDIARYIP>

#This command works almost the same above with the difference that with the -D flag it enables a SocksProxy at the <LISTENINGPORT> which forwards sockets to a target machine through the intermediary machine. We can interact witht he target machine through proxy chains but first we have to modify /etc/proxychains4.conf with the IP hosting the SocksProxy and the port.

#Example; ssh -N -D 0.0.0.0:9999 database_admin@10.4.50.215


#BOTH COMMANDS WORKS IN WINDOWS AND LINUX.
